const PI =3.14;
PI =42;

1. the difference between var and let is that var will hoist to the top of the scope but not let.
let is block scoped variable. if declared inside a code block, cannot be called outside.
var can be reassigned and redeclared, let can only be reassigned.

2. the difference between var and const is var will hoist to the top.
const is also block scoped variable. cannot be redeclared or reassigned.

3. difference between let and const is let can be reassigned but const cannot.

4. hoisting is when delcare through var, the variable will be declared at the top and then assigned the value at the orginal code place.